<h2>What's Eardogger?</h2>

<p>Eardogger is a bookmarking service for long webcomics and web-books.</p>

<p>There are lots of ways to bookmark a web page, but this one is weird because it's designed for <em>reading:</em></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Only one bookmark per site.</strong> A marked page is just a temporary resting point in a larger work; when you read a little further and save your place again, Eardogger moves your old bookmark. In other words, Eardogger does the "yesterday's bus ticket" type of bookmark, not the "six colors of sticky notes" type.</li>
  <li><strong>Available everywhere.</strong> Pause your reading on one device, resume wherever.</li>
  <li><strong>Incredibly lazy.</strong> Pause or resume with one click on sites you've bookmarked before.</li>
